The paper discusses the stability of algorithms, which is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science. However, the focus on analyzing and visualizing time-varying data suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of Euclidean minimum spanning trees also supports this hypothesis. Other possible sub-categories include data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI), as these fields also deal with algorithmic stability and analysis.
